        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Although there are also use cases for `:restart` without a UI. Currently that still enters the main loop, but doesn't execute `[command]` until a UI is attached. If the new server waits for UI, it'll never enter the main loop before that, which may break some use cases?\n\nOr perhaps `:restart` should preserve whether `--headless` was originally specified? Or it should add `--headless` if and only if executed without a UI?",
            "created_at": "2026-03-29T21:21:05Z",
